    "en": "In patients with ischaemic stroke who are very high risk (defined as stroke plus another major atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease or stroke plus multiple high-risk conditions), are taking maximally tolerated statin and ezetimibe therapy and still have an LDL-C >70 mg/dL, it is reasonable to treat with PCSK9 inhibitor therapy.",
